subcellularLocation.summary: Localized to nucleus, plasma membrane and cytoplasm.

tissueExpression.summary: Most normal cells showed moderate to strong cytoplasmic positivity. Prostate, glial cells and spleen were weakly stained or negative.
Most malignant cells displayed moderate cytoplasmic staining. Most non-Hodgkins lymphomas as well as several prostate and renal cancers were strongly stained.

tissueExpression.summary: Moderate cytoplasmic and/or nuclear positivity was observed in most normal tissues. The intestine and placental trophoblastic cells were strongly immunoreactive. Staining of luminal membranes was for example observed in prostate and the intestine. Spleen, endometrial stroma and pancreatic islets were negative.

Malignant cells showed weak to moderate positivity in cytoplasm often in combination with nucleus and /or membrane. Occasional cases of prostate and pancreatic cancers were strongly stained. Non Hodgkin's lymphomas were negative.
